mil.navy.nrl.cmf.sousa.spatiotemporal
Interface Queryable

All Known Subinterfaces:
CalcDB
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractCalcDB, CityQueryable, ModelQueryable, RasterQueryable, TrailQueryable
public interface Queryable

Queryable is an interface to a spatiotemporal search engine. Searches return Sets of QueryResultHandle. One Set contains things that are no longer within the spatiotemporal search region. The other Set returns things that are new to the spatiotemporal search region.

As a spatiotemporal region moves around in space-time, it loses and acquires members.

Answers a spatiotemporal query and determines what objects are no longer in the spatiotemporal region (removed)and what objects are new members of the region (added).

By convention, the components of each Vector3d encode the physical location in the following way:

  • x is degrees latitude.
  • y is degrees longitude.
  • z is elevation in meters relative to sealevel. (For example, 0 is sealevel, -1 is 1 meter below sealevel, 1 is 1 meter above sealevel.)

      Parameters:
      lowerLeftCorner - spatial lower left corner of the search region
      width - spatial width of the search region
      timeLowerBound - lower bound on time of the search region
      timeUpperBound - upper bound on time of the search region
      previous - the Set returned by the previous call to query
      fieldNames - the keys of each QueryResultHandle
      added - the QueryResultHandles of things that are new to the search region.
      removed - the QueryResultHandles of things that are no longer in the search region.
      context - a Map in which the implementation keeps per-client state. The caller must create the Map and must not change it.
      Returns:
      a Set of QueryResultHandle
